  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Independent Monitoring of Forest Law Enforcement and Governance (IM-FLEG) in the Democratic Republic of Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project, led by UK based NGO REM, provides an independent view of forest logging practices in the DRC and the legal and administrative framework to regulate them. Strengthening forest governance is part of the FLEGT Program discussions between DRC and the European Union, to combat illegal logging of tropical forests. The Congolese state has, with this project, engaged in a process designed to strengthen its law enforcement in order to guarantee the legality of the timber exported to the European market place.  Our main objective is to contribute to the realization of the principles of good governance in forestry activities and provide support to the improvement of forest law enforcement.  We do this by: 1) supporting the development of a law enforcement strategy and development of procedures within the forest ministry; 2) observing the application of forest law enforcement procedures;
3) observing the follow-up of forest exploitation illegalities and sanctions by the ministry;
4) ensuring publication of information relating to forest exploitation and governance;
5) ensuring the sustainability of independent monitoring through the participation of civil society.</narrative>
  </description>
